 Chawla stars in innings win

 Under 19 Test vs NZ 

Mumbai: Leg-spinner Piyush Chawla and pacer Abu Nachim shared eight wickets to power India to an innings-and-50-run win in the first under-19 Test in Lincoln on Wednesday. 

According to information received here, skipper Chawla followed up his century in the first innings with a haul of five for 19, while Nachim took three for 55 as New Zealand were bundled out for 147 in their second innings. 

Ishant Sharma took five wickets as the New Zealand colts replied with 302. 

The second match of the series will be played in Dunedin from January 27. 

BRIEF SCORES 

India U-19 499/8 dec. (Piyush Chawla 119, Virat Koli 113, Ravi Teja 105, Yomahesh 61, Ajinkya Rahane 49). New Zealand 302 (Ishant Sharma 5/55) amp; 147 (M. Taiaroa 42; P. Chawla 5/19, Abu Nacheem 3/55). India won by an innings amp; 50 runs. 

